#
# ============================================================================
# COMMIT MESSAGE CONVENTION (Conventional Commits)
# ============================================================================
#
# TYPE (required):
#   feat:     New feature (correlates with MINOR in SemVer)
#   fix:      Bug fix (correlates with PATCH in SemVer)
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   style:    Formatting, missing semicolons, etc (no code change)
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf:     Performance improvement
#   test:     Adding or correcting tests
#   chore:    Build process, dependencies, CI/CD
#   ci:       CI configuration changes
#   revert:   Reverts a previous commit
#
# SCOPE (optional):
#   frontend: Next.js frontend changes
#   agent:    Python LangGraph agent changes
#   db:       Database migrations, RLS policies
#   auth:     Authentication flow changes
#   api:      API routes or endpoints
#   ui:       UI components only
#   deps:     Dependency updates
#
# SUBJECT (required):
#   - Use imperative mood: "add" not "added" or "adds"
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No period at the end
#   - Max 50 characters
#
# BODY (optional):
#   - Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#   - Can use bullet points
#
# FOOTER (optional):
#   - Reference issues: Fixes #123, Closes #456
#   - Reference spec: Spec: 001-user-auth
#   - Breaking changes: BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
#
# ============================================================================
# EXAMPLES
# ============================================================================
#
# feat(frontend): add user profile avatar upload
#
# Users can now upload custom avatars from the profile page.
# Avatars are stored in Supabase Storage with RLS policies.
#
# Spec: 003-user-profiles
# Closes #45
#
# ============================================================================
#
# fix(agent): handle timeout in tavily search
#
# The search was hanging indefinitely when Tavily API was slow.
# Added 10-second timeout with graceful error handling.
#
# Fixes #78
